artifacts.name: Mercedes 300SL Gullwing
artifacts.description: This was the fastest production car in 1957. With blood red interiors and silver body, it is still the best looking convertible in the world.

artifacts.name: Cadillac Series 62 Convertible Coupe
artifacts.description: The 1941 Cadillac was a masterpiece of subtle, flowing curves that began with a bold and distinctive grille design with the horsepower of 150.

artifacts.name: 1937 Rolls-Royce 25/30 Sedanca
artifacts.description: 1937 Rolls Royce 25/30 Sedanca in black exterior over Black Leather and Tan Cloth Interior with a mileage of 51,971.

artifacts.name: 1895 Panhard et Levassor
artifacts.description: Engine in front, gearbox behind it, drive to the rear wheels, this layout gave the world the first automobile.

artifacts.name: Ford Model T
artifacts.description: The Ford Model T was named the most influential car of the 20th century in the 1999 Car of the Century competition. This car was also used in Flinstones picture production in Hollywood.

artifacts.name: Mercedes-Benz 300 SLR (W 196 S) racing sports car,
artifacts.description: With the 300 SLR (W 196 S) Mercedes-Benz wins the Sports Car World Championship in 1955. The vehicle is basically a Type W 196 R Formula One racing car with a two-seater sports car body. It also won the Eifel race, the Swedish Grand Prix and the Targa Florio (Sicily)

artifacts.name: Alfa Romeo 8C 2300 Zagato
artifacts.description: Alfa Romeo 8C 2300 Zagato won the 360-mile race on the famed Grande Circuit. It has also been used in Mission Impossible 2 and 3 Hollywood movie.

artifacts.name: Jaguar E-Type
artifacts.description: It is a British sports car that was manufactured by Jaguar Cars Ltd in 1961. Its combination of beauty and high performance establish the model as an icon of the motoring world.

artifacts.name: Cadillac Sixteen Madame X Club Sedan
artifacts.description: The flair of the Madame X gives it a coveted place in the Full Classic pecking order, akin more to the open-top Cadillacs rather than the upright sedans. This car in its attractive colors is a very nice example of a very desirable 16-cylinder American classic.

artifacts.name: Cord
artifacts.description: It was the first front-wheel-drive American production car and it was also the first car driven by scooby doo in one of his most popular TV shows.

artifacts.name: Horch
artifacts.description: Horch model is a world-class—pricier and rarer than the famous Mercedes-Benz 540K Special Roadster—and is almost impossible to buy. This is exclusively to be bought by the king.

artifacts.name: Napier
artifacts.description: Six-cylinder Napier, which arrived for 1904, challenged Rolls-Royce in quality and price. This car has been with all the famous hollywood celebrities from Tom Cruise, Beyonce and now Rihanna. Selling only for the king

artifacts.name: Stutz
artifacts.description: This car had the four-valve, 80-hp “T-Head” engine of 1911, and was one of the strongest cars in Europe at the time. The king of India called this car his favorite car in the world.

artifacts.name: Chrysler Imperial
artifacts.description: This is the rarest car found on the planet Earth. This is a custom built Chrysler car and there are only 3 of these in the world.

artifacts.name: 1940 Packard
artifacts.description: This was the first car in the world to have a front-end, fully integrated heating, ventilating, and air-conditioning system.

artifacts.name: Ford F100 Pickup
artifacts.description: This was the first truck produced by Ford that had a bed at the back of the truck.

artifacts.name: 1952 oldsmobile
artifacts.description: This car was owned by the creator of Mickey Mouse, Walt Disney. This was his first and the most favorite car.

artifacts.name: 1937 Lincoln Zephyr
artifacts.description: The Lincoln-Zephyr is a line of luxury cars that was produced by the Lincoln division of Ford from 1936 to 1942. This was called the  god of the west wind because it was the fastest car of its type.

artifacts.name: Ferrari 250 GTO
artifacts.description: This is the most expensive car in the world. It is made by Ferrari and there are only 32 of these made in the world.
